# CODEOWNERS — review ownership for security-sensitive paths.
#
# Codex 2026-05-08 (Wave 9 #2 MEDIUM-LOW) — repo previously had no
# CODEOWNERS file; workflow files and security-sensitive code paths
# had no owner-review gate. With this file in place, GitHub UI will
# request a review from the listed owner whenever a PR touches a
# matching path. To make it BLOCKING, set
# `require_code_owner_reviews: true` in the main branch protection
# (see https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-security/managing-protected-branches/about-protected-branches#require-pull-request-reviews-before-merging).
#
# Today this is a single-founder repo, so the owner is always
# @Igotsty1e. The file's value is not in second-pair-of-eyes review
# (the founder is both author and reviewer) — it's in:
#
#   1. Documenting which paths are security-critical (just reading
#      this file shows the trust surface map).
#   2. Future-proofing: when a teammate joins, ownership migrations
#      are a CODEOWNERS edit, not a "where do I add this?" hunt.
#   3. Catching accidental cross-cuts: if a refactor PR touches both
#      lib/payments and lib/scheduling, the GitHub UI surfaces
#      multiple owner cohorts in one place.
#
# Format reference: https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-security/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners

# Default — every path that doesn't match a more specific rule below.
*                                  @Igotsty1e

# CI / CD configuration. Changes here affect every deploy.
/.github/                          @Igotsty1e
/scripts/                          @Igotsty1e

# Security primitives. The trust boundary lives here — every change
# warrants extra care.
/lib/security/                     @Igotsty1e
/lib/auth/                         @Igotsty1e
/lib/audit/                        @Igotsty1e
/lib/db/                           @Igotsty1e

# Payment surface. Money-moving code; webhook handlers, slot binding,
# receipt-token gate. Regulated by 152-ФЗ + 54-ФЗ.
/lib/payments/                     @Igotsty1e
/app/api/payments/                 @Igotsty1e

# Schema / migrations. Schema changes are forever — review before
# applying anywhere.
/migrations/                       @Igotsty1e

# Legal / consent surface. Any change to public-facing offer, privacy,
# or consent text touches consumer-protection regulations.
/app/offer/                        @Igotsty1e
/app/privacy/                      @Igotsty1e
/app/consent/                      @Igotsty1e
/lib/legal/                        @Igotsty1e

# Admin surface. Privileged routes; any new path here needs a fresh
# look at role guards.
/app/api/admin/                    @Igotsty1e
/app/admin/                        @Igotsty1e

# Slot booking — separate trust boundary from payments.
/lib/scheduling/                   @Igotsty1e
/app/api/slots/                    @Igotsty1e
